BT 0.5 g /F1 10 Tf 282.0 740 Td (Chapter 14) Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 16 Tf 248.4 720 Td (SLEEP FOR TEENS) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (During puberty, your body's internal clock shifts later. You naturally want to) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 665 Td (stay up later and sleep in later. This is biology, not laziness! Your brain) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 650 Td (releases the sleep hormone melatonin later at night during puberty.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 635 Td (Unfortunately, school start times do not adjust to match.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 608 Td (You need 9-11 hours of sleep during puberty. Your body does its most important) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 593 Td (growing and repairing during sleep. Growth hormone is released primarily during) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 578 Td (deep sleep. Not getting enough sleep can affect your mood, grades, skin, weight,) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 563 Td (and immune system.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 536 Td (Tips for better sleep: keep a consistent bedtime \(even on weekends\), stop) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 521 Td (screens 30-60 minutes before bed \(blue light blocks melatonin\), keep your room) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 506 Td (cool and dark, avoid caffeine after noon, and create a relaxing bedtime routine.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 479 Td (If you cannot fall asleep: try deep breathing, progressive muscle relaxation, or) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (listening to calm music. Write worries in a journal before bed to get them out) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 449 Td (of your head. Avoid looking at the clock because it increases anxiety about not) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 434 Td (sleeping.) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 407 Td (Sleep is not negotiable for a developing brain and body. Think of it as) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 392 Td (recharging your phone. If you only charge to 50 percent, you will not make it) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 11 Tf 72 377 Td (through the day. Give your body the full charge it needs.) Tj ET

endstream
